The available evidence describes somatostatin receptor scintigraphy (e.g., with indium-111 pentetreotide or technetium-99m depreotide) as a validated imaging modality that detects tumors expressing somatostatin receptors. It does not mention any direct comparative data linking immunohistochemical staining for somatostatin receptor subtype 2a to improved prediction of response over scintigraphic uptake. Since scintigraphy provides non-invasive whole-body assessment and correlates strongly with receptor expression, there is no evidence suggesting additional value from IHC-specific subtype 2a analysis in predicting response.

